#required directory structure

snpeffdata
    └── GCF_004118075.1_ASM411807v1_snpeff
        ├── genes.gff -> /data/norman/resources/Cowpea/GCF_004118075.1_ASM411807v1/GCF_004118075.1_ASM411807v1_genomic.gff
        ├── genes.gtf -> /data/norman/resources/Cowpea/GCF_004118075.1_ASM411807v1/GCF_004118075.1_ASM411807v1_genomic.gtf
        ├── protein.fa -> /data/norman/resources/Cowpea/GCF_004118075.1_ASM411807v1/GCF_004118075.1_ASM411807v1_protein.faa
        ├── sequences.fa -> /data/norman/resources/Cowpea/GCF_004118075.1_ASM411807v1/GCF_004118075.1_ASM411807v1_genomic.fna
        └── snpEffectPredictor.bin

# under snpeffdata/ add directories corresponding to your genomes, append "_snpeff" to avoid confusion. You will have to have "sequence.fa" and "genes.gff" or "genes.gtf"; "protein.fa" is optional. They can/should be softlinks.

"snpEffectPredictor.bin" is the actual database and needs to be be generated by snpeff build. E.g.,

$ snpEff build –gff3 genomes_and_annotations/snpeffdata/<reference-genome>_snpeff
